            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'Restorative Reproductive Medicine (RRM) is an approach within conventional medicine that works cooperatively with the body to diagnose and treat the underlying causes of reproductive health conditions. Unlike approaches that mask symptoms with hormonal medications or bypass natural function with assisted reproductive technologies, RRM uses standard and advanced diagnostic tools to investigate the root cause, whether hormonal, anatomical, or inflammatory, and restore natural function.',
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'What conditions does RRM treat?',
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'RRM commonly addresses endometriosis, polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS), unexplained infertility, recurrent miscarriage, irregular or painful periods, premenstrual syndrome, hormonal imbalances, ovulatory dysfunction, and pelvic pain. Treatment may include medical management, hormonal support, surgical intervention, or a combination tailored to the underlying diagnosis.',
          },
        },
