          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'How effective is RRM for infertility?',
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'Published research shows RRM treatment followed by timed intercourse has achieved live birth rates of 29-41% depending on age and diagnosis. For women under 35, rates reach 34%, and for women with BMI under 25, rates reach 40%. RRM combined with surgical treatment of moderate-to-severe endometriosis has shown pregnancy rates of 55% per woman. Results vary by condition and individual factors.',
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'Is RRM covered by insurance?',
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'Many RRM treatments are covered by standard health insurance because they involve conventional medical diagnostics (bloodwork, imaging, ultrasound) and treatments (medications, surgery) for diagnosed conditions. Unlike IVF, which requires specific fertility coverage, RRM treatments are often coded as treatment for endometriosis, PCOS, hormonal disorders, or other diagnosed conditions. Coverage varies by plan and provider.',
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'What is NaProTechnology?',
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'NaProTechnology (Natural Procreative Technology) is a specific type of Restorative Reproductive Medicine developed at the Saint Paul VI Institute. It uses the Creighton Model FertilityCare System to monitor biomarkers, identify reproductive health problems, and guide targeted medical and surgical treatment. NaProTechnology is practiced by physicians with specialized fellowship training.',
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'How do I find an RRM doctor?',
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'RRM-trained physicians can be found through the International Institute for Restorative Reproductive Medicine (IIRRM) provider directory, FertilityCare Centers of America, or by searching for NaProTechnology-trained physicians in your area. RRM Academy also provides educational resources to help you understand what to look for in a provider and what questions to ask.',
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: 'Can RRM help with endometriosis?',
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: 'Yes. RRM addresses endometriosis through a combination of thorough diagnosis (often using advanced imaging and surgical evaluation), excision surgery to remove endometriotic tissue, and long-term medical management to prevent recurrence. A meta-analysis found that surgical treatment of moderate-to-severe endometriosis yielded a 55.3% per-woman pregnancy rate, compared to 9.9% with IVF alone in similar cases.',
          },
        },
